//Closures example

function createCounter() {
  let x = 0; // private variable

  function display() {
    return ++x;
  }

  return display;
}

const counter = createCounter();

counter(); // 1
counter(); // 2
counter(); // 3

Why This Is a Closure (Explain This Confidently)

Say this in interviews ğŸ‘‡

â€œdisplay forms a closure over the variable x.
Even after createCounter finishes execution, display still has access to x due to lexical scoping.
This allows data privacy because x cannot be accessed directly from outside.â€

This explanation is exactly what interviewers expect.
